44// WebRtcVoiceEngine is a class to be used with CompositeMediaEngine.
45// It uses the WebRtc VoiceEngine library for audio handling.
46class WebRtcVoiceEngine final : public VoiceEngineInterface {
47 friend class WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel;
48
49 public:
50 WebRtcVoiceEngine(
51 webrtc::TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
52 webrtc::AudioDeviceModule* adm,
53 const rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioEncoderFactory>& encoder_factory,
54 const rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioDecoderFactory>& decoder_factory,
55 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioMixer> audio_mixer,
56 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioProcessing> audio_processing,
57 webrtc::AudioFrameProcessor* audio_frame_processor,
58 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials);
59
60 WebRtcVoiceEngine() = delete;
61 WebRtcVoiceEngine(const WebRtcVoiceEngine&) = delete;
62 WebRtcVoiceEngine& operator=(const WebRtcVoiceEngine&) = delete;
63
64 ~WebRtcVoiceEngine() override;
65
66 // Does initialization that needs to occur on the worker thread.
67 void Init() override;
68
69 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioState> GetAudioState() const override;
70 VoiceMediaChannel* CreateMediaChannel(
71 webrtc::Call* call,
72 const MediaConfig& config,
73 const AudioOptions& options,
74 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options) override;
75
76 const std::vector<AudioCodec>& send_codecs() const override;
77 const std::vector<AudioCodec>& recv_codecs() const override;
78 std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> GetRtpHeaderExtensions()
79 const override;
80
81 // Starts AEC dump using an existing file. A maximum file size in bytes can be
82 // specified. When the maximum file size is reached, logging is stopped and
83 // the file is closed. If max_size_bytes is set to <= 0, no limit will be
84 // used.
85 bool StartAecDump(webrtc::FileWrapper file, int64_t max_size_bytes) override;
86
87 // Stops AEC dump.
88 void StopAecDump() override;
89
90 private:
91 // Every option that is "set" will be applied. Every option not "set" will be
92 // ignored. This allows us to selectively turn on and off different options
93 // easily at any time.
94 bool ApplyOptions(const AudioOptions& options);
95
96 int CreateVoEChannel();
97
98 webrtc::TaskQueueFactory* const task_queue_factory_;
99 std::unique_ptr<rtc::TaskQueue> low_priority_worker_queue_;
100
101 webrtc::AudioDeviceModule* adm();
102 webrtc::AudioProcessing* apm() const;
103 webrtc::AudioState* audio_state();
104
105 std::vector<AudioCodec> CollectCodecs(
106 const std::vector<webrtc::AudioCodecSpec>& specs) const;
107
108 webrtc::SequenceChecker signal_thread_checker_;
109 webrtc::SequenceChecker worker_thread_checker_;
110
111 // The audio device module.
112 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioDeviceModule> adm_;
113 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioEncoderFactory> encoder_factory_;
114 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioDecoderFactory> decoder_factory_;
115 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioMixer> audio_mixer_;
116 // The audio processing module.
117 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioProcessing> apm_;
118 // Asynchronous audio processing.
119 webrtc::AudioFrameProcessor* const audio_frame_processor_;
120 // The primary instance of WebRtc VoiceEngine.
121 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioState> audio_state_;
122 std::vector<AudioCodec> send_codecs_;
123 std::vector<AudioCodec> recv_codecs_;
124 bool is_dumping_aec_ = false;
125 bool initialized_ = false;
126
127 // Cache experimental_ns and apply in case they are missing in the audio
128 // options.
129 absl::optional<bool> experimental_ns_;
130 // Jitter buffer settings for new streams.
131 size_t audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets_ = 200;
132 bool audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate_ = false;
133 int audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms_ = 0;
134 bool audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling_ = false;
135
136 // If this field trial is enabled, we will negotiate and use RFC 2198
137 // redundancy for opus audio.
138 const bool audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_;
139 const bool minimized_remsampling_on_mobile_trial_enabled_;
140};
141
142// WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel is an implementation of VoiceMediaChannel that uses
143// WebRtc Voice Engine.
144class WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel final : public VoiceMediaChannel,
145 public webrtc::Transport {
146 public:
147 WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel(WebRtcVoiceEngine* engine,
148 const MediaConfig& config,
149 const AudioOptions& options,
150 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
151 webrtc::Call* call);
152
153 WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel() = delete;
154 WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel(const WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel&) = delete;
155 WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel& operator=(const WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel&) = delete;
156
157 ~WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel() override;
158
159 const AudioOptions& options() const { return options_; }
160
161 bool SetSendParameters(const AudioSendParameters& params) override;
162 bool SetRecvParameters(const AudioRecvParameters& params) override;
163 webrtc::RtpParameters GetRtpSendParameters(uint32_t ssrc) const override;
164 webrtc::RTCError SetRtpSendParameters(
165 uint32_t ssrc,
166 const webrtc::RtpParameters& parameters) override;
167 webrtc::RtpParameters GetRtpReceiveParameters(uint32_t ssrc) const override;
168 webrtc::RtpParameters GetDefaultRtpReceiveParameters() const override;
169
170 void SetPlayout(bool playout) override;
171 void SetSend(bool send) override;
172 bool SetAudioSend(uint32_t ssrc,
173 bool enable,
174 const AudioOptions* options,
175 AudioSource* source) override;
176 bool AddSendStream(const StreamParams& sp) override;
177 bool RemoveSendStream(uint32_t ssrc) override;
178 bool AddRecvStream(const StreamParams& sp) override;
179 bool RemoveRecvStream(uint32_t ssrc) override;
180 void ResetUnsignaledRecvStream() override;
181 void OnDemuxerCriteriaUpdatePending() override;
182 void OnDemuxerCriteriaUpdateComplete() override;
183
184 // E2EE Frame API
185 // Set a frame decryptor to a particular ssrc that will intercept all
186 // incoming audio payloads and attempt to decrypt them before forwarding the
187 // result.
188 void SetFrameDecryptor(uint32_t ssrc,
189 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameDecryptorInterface>
190 frame_decryptor) override;
191 // Set a frame encryptor to a particular ssrc that will intercept all
192 // outgoing audio payloads frames and attempt to encrypt them and forward the
193 // result to the packetizer.
194 void SetFrameEncryptor(uint32_t ssrc,
195 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameEncryptorInterface>
196 frame_encryptor) override;
197
198 bool SetOutputVolume(uint32_t ssrc, double volume) override;
199 // Applies the new volume to current and future unsignaled streams.
200 bool SetDefaultOutputVolume(double volume) override;
201
202 bool SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(uint32_t ssrc, int delay_ms) override;
203 absl::optional<int> GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(
204 uint32_t ssrc) const override;
205
206 bool CanInsertDtmf() override;
207 bool InsertDtmf(uint32_t ssrc, int event, int duration) override;
208
209 void OnPacketReceived(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
210 int64_t packet_time_us) override;
211 void OnPacketSent(const rtc::SentPacket& sent_packet) override;
212 void OnNetworkRouteChanged(const std::string& transport_name,
213 const rtc::NetworkRoute& network_route) override;
214 void OnReadyToSend(bool ready) override;
215 bool GetStats(VoiceMediaInfo* info, bool get_and_clear_legacy_stats) override;
216
217 // Set the audio sink for an existing stream.
218 void SetRawAudioSink(
219 uint32_t ssrc,
220 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> sink) override;
221 // Will set the audio sink on the latest unsignaled stream, future or
222 // current. Only one stream at a time will use the sink.
223 void SetDefaultRawAudioSink(
224 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> sink) override;
225
226 std::vector<webrtc::RtpSource> GetSources(uint32_t ssrc) const override;
227
228 // Sets a frame transformer between encoder and packetizer, to transform
229 // encoded frames before sending them out the network.
230 void SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
231 uint32_t ssrc,
232 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer)
233 override;
234 void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
235 uint32_t ssrc,
236 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer)
237 override;
238
239 // implements Transport interface
240 bool SendRtp(const uint8_t* data,
241 size_t len,
242 const webrtc::PacketOptions& options) override;
243
244 bool SendRtcp(const uint8_t* data, size_t len) override;
245
246 private:
247 bool SetOptions(const AudioOptions& options);
248 bool SetRecvCodecs(const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs);
249 bool SetSendCodecs(const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs);
250 bool SetLocalSource(uint32_t ssrc, AudioSource* source);
251 bool MuteStream(uint32_t ssrc, bool mute);
252
253 WebRtcVoiceEngine* engine() { return engine_; }
254 int CreateVoEChannel();
255 bool DeleteVoEChannel(int channel);
256 bool SetMaxSendBitrate(int bps);
257 void SetupRecording();
258 // Check if 'ssrc' is an unsignaled stream, and if so mark it as not being
259 // unsignaled anymore (i.e. it is now removed, or signaled), and return true.
260 bool MaybeDeregisterUnsignaledRecvStream(uint32_t ssrc);
261
262 webrtc::TaskQueueBase* const worker_thread_;
263 webrtc::ScopedTaskSafety task_safety_;
264 webrtc::SequenceChecker network_thread_checker_;
265
266 WebRtcVoiceEngine* const engine_ = nullptr;
267 std::vector<AudioCodec> send_codecs_;
268
269 // TODO(kwiberg): decoder_map_ and recv_codecs_ store the exact same
270 // information, in slightly different formats. Eliminate recv_codecs_.
271 std::map<int, webrtc::SdpAudioFormat> decoder_map_;
272 std::vector<AudioCodec> recv_codecs_;
273
274 int max_send_bitrate_bps_ = 0;
275 AudioOptions options_;
276 absl::optional<int> dtmf_payload_type_;
277 int dtmf_payload_freq_ = -1;
278 bool recv_transport_cc_enabled_ = false;
279 bool recv_nack_enabled_ = false;
280 bool playout_ = false;
281 bool send_ = false;
282 webrtc::Call* const call_ = nullptr;
283
284 const MediaConfig::Audio audio_config_;
285
286 // Queue of unsignaled SSRCs; oldest at the beginning.
287 std::vector<uint32_t> unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_;
288
289 // This is a stream param that comes from the remote description, but wasn't
290 // signaled with any a=ssrc lines. It holds the information that was signaled
291 // before the unsignaled receive stream is created when the first packet is
292 // received.
293 StreamParams unsignaled_stream_params_;
294
295 // Volume for unsignaled streams, which may be set before the stream exists.
296 double default_recv_volume_ = 1.0;
297
298 // Delay for unsignaled streams, which may be set before the stream exists.
299 int default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms_ = 0;
300
301 // Sink for latest unsignaled stream - may be set before the stream exists.
302 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> default_sink_;
303 // Default SSRC to use for RTCP receiver reports in case of no signaled
304 // send streams. See: https://code.google.com/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=4740
305 // and https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=547661
306 uint32_t receiver_reports_ssrc_ = 0xFA17FA17u;
307
308 class WebRtcAudioSendStream;
309 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcAudioSendStream*> send_streams_;
310 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> send_rtp_extensions_;
311 std::string mid_;
312
313 class WebRtcAudioReceiveStream;
314 std::map<uint32_t, WebRtcAudioReceiveStream*> recv_streams_;
315 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> recv_rtp_extensions_;
316
317 absl::optional<webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config::SendCodecSpec>
318 send_codec_spec_;
319
320 // TODO(kwiberg): Per-SSRC codec pair IDs?
321 const webrtc::AudioCodecPairId codec_pair_id_ =
322 webrtc::AudioCodecPairId::Create();
323
324 // Per peer connection crypto options that last for the lifetime of the peer
325 // connection.
326 const webrtc::CryptoOptions crypto_options_;
327 // Unsignaled streams have an option to have a frame decryptor set on them.
328 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameDecryptorInterface>
329 unsignaled_frame_decryptor_;
330
331 const bool audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_;
332};
333} // namespace cricket

335#endif // MEDIA_ENGINE_WEBRTC_VOICE_ENGINE_H_
